Subject: Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs (1912 play) 
To: Bert
Content:
Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs is a Broadway play that debuted at the Little Theatre on West 44th Street, New York City, on October 31, 1912. Based on the stories by the Brothers Grimm, it was produced by Winthrop Ames who had written it under the pseudonym "Jessie Graham White." The play met with favorable reviews.
